# Details

Your input `&quot;2020-12-30T17:30:00Z&quot;` is in standard ISO 8601 format. The `Z` on the end means an offset-from-UTC of zero hours-minute-seconds, and is pronounced “Zulu”. We also refer to a Zulu date-time as being &quot;in UTC&quot;. 

You should parse such inputs as an `Instant`, not the `ZonedDateTime` seen in your Question.

    Instant instant = Instant.parse( &quot;2020-12-30T17:30:00Z&quot; ) ;

To see that same moment through the wall-clock time (offset) used by the people of a particular region, specify a time zone (`ZoneId`) to produce a `ZonedDateTime`.

